		<h2>Passages</h2>
		As part of the week-long orientation program, new students participate in a two day outing to the Hood Canal area of Washington. Groups of 8-10 student choose from an array of activities that include hiking, canoing, backpacking, and several other options. This program, known as Passages, helps develop acquaintances during the first nervous week of college. To find out more about this nationally acclaimed orientation program, <a href = "http://www.pugetsound.edu/student-life/student-activities/puget-sound-outdoors/">Click here.</a>
		
