  	<h2>Visit Mount Rainier</h2>

  	Mount Rainier stands at just over 14,400 feet, overshadowing the sea-level landscape in Seattle and Tacoma. The Carbon River and Paradise entrances are less than two hours from University of Puget Sound. One of Washington's prized gems, Rainier offers some of the most beautiful wilderness in the Pacific Northwest. Below is a real-time feed of Mount Rainier from Paradise Valley. More information about seasonal closures, weather conditions, directions, and park events can be found on the <a href = "http://www.nps.gov/mora/index.htm">National Park Service's website.</a>
  	


